CHANGELOG.md:273:- Added the CypherClaw narrative API regression suite plus a minimal auth gate (T-005@20260502T001347Z): `cypherclaw.narrative_api.create_app(...)` now accepts an optional `auth_token` keyword that, when set, requires every endpoint to carry a matching `X-Narrative-Auth` header (missing/wrong → 401); empty/unset preserves the existing auth-disabled behavior so T-010's env-var pull and startup warning land cleanly. `tests/test_narrative_api_memory.py` and `tests/test_narrative_api_events.py` now pin the four scenario floors (success path, auth failure when enabled, bad input validation, downstream-engine error handling) for `POST /memory/search`, `GET /events`, and `POST /events`, plus 503 fallback behavior when the deploy-side `cypherclaw.narrative.{memory,events}` package is absent and append-returns-None record synthesis. `pytest --cov=cypherclaw.narrative_api` reports 84% module coverage.
CHANGELOG.md:295:- Added a live Replicate smoke test for the generation backend (T-005): `tests/test_generation_live_replicate.py` exercises `ReplicateClient.generate(req)` against the real Replicate API with a fixed prompt and seed, and asserts a >100 KB WAV payload, `cost_usd` inside `[$0.01, $0.50]`, and `latency_ms < 60000`. The test is gated behind both the new `--run-live-replicate` pytest flag (registered in `tests/conftest.py` alongside the existing `--run-live-modal` seam) and a non-empty `REPLICATE_API_TOKEN`, so the default `pytest tests/` run skips it. Documented as ~$0.10 per opted-in run.
CHANGELOG.md:331:- Added live-buffer and sample-bank abstractions for SenseWeave inputs: new `live_buffer.py` module provides `LiveBuffer` for stable real-time environmental audio state (source name, capture path, freshness, RMS, spectral profile, transform history) and `SampleBankArchive` for retaining selected clips to archive storage with JSON metadata sidecars.
CHANGELOG.md:376:- Swapped the self-listener toward a host-stable monitor path: `self_listener.py` now prefers a PipeWire sink monitor target when one is available, still falls back to direct JACK or `pw-jack` port capture when needed, and keeps the old backend cache/reprobe logic only as fallback behavior instead of the primary live path.
CHANGELOG.md:381:- Hardened the sample-playback daemon so stable ambient scenes can refresh repeatedly after cooldown instead of firing once per unchanged signature, and render failures now write a structured error state instead of crashing the loop.
CHANGELOG.md:393:- Wired stable EMSD sample capture into the live runtime: added `capture_alias.py` plus `sample_dsp_activity.py`, taught `room_listener.py`, `contact_listener.py`, `theramini_listener.py`, and `self_listener.py` to mirror fresh clips into `/tmp/room_capture.wav`, `/tmp/contact_capture.wav`, `/tmp/theramini_capture.wav`, and `/tmp/self_capture.wav`, and made `self_listener.py` publish `/tmp/sample_dsp_activity.json` with concrete activity modes, trigger flags, and DSP/sample-control values derived from composer, cadence, and sensor state.
CHANGELOG.md:394:- Expanded CypherClaw boot coverage for the EMSD sampler path: `cypherclaw_boot.sh` now starts `theramini_listener.py` and `contact_listener.py` alongside the room listener so the stable sample aliases can refresh during unattended startup instead of remaining planned-but-missing files.
CHANGELOG.md:460:- Added the missing `OPT-005` half-hour Telegram heartbeat in the live daemon scheduler, including uptime, I/O wait, memory, load, available-agent count, queue progress, pet XP summary, and Observatory logging.
